Miasma		KEY:xxx ~ 				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:xxx Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:Starting at 9th level, if a creature is within the necromancer's fear aura at the beginning of its turn, the creature must succeed at a Fortitude save with a DC 10 + half the necromancer's level + his Charisma modifier or become sickened for 1 round. A creature of the animal, fey, or plant type that fails its save is nauseated for 1 round and sickened for 1 minute thereafter. If the creature makes its save, it is immune to this effect for 24 hours, as are creatures immune to disease.
Clear Mind		KEY:xxx ~ 				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:xxx Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:At 10th level, a necromancer can regain his MP quicker. The necromancer must be relaxed and must be free from overt distractions, such as combat raging nearby or other loud noises. The necromancer regains MP equaling his Charisma modifier per hour.
Fortification		KEY:xxx ~ 				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:xxx Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:Starting at 10th level, a necromancer gains light fortification (25%% immunity to critical hits). At 17th level, the necromancer gains moderate fortification (50%% immunity to critical hits).
Undead Mastery		KEY:xxx ~ 				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:xxx Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Supernatural	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:All undead creatures created by a necromancer who has reached 11th level or higher gain a +4 enhancement bonus to Strength and Dexterity and 2 additional hit points per Hit Die.
Master of Death		KEY:xxx ~ 				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:xxx Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Supernatural	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:As the necromancer comes closer and closer to his ultimate ascension into undeath, he also becomes more aware of how weak he used to be. When activating this ability, upon reaching 12th level, he may choose between body and mind. Master of death lasts for a number of rounds equal to the necromancer's caster level. He may use this ability one time per day per four necromancer levels he possesses.
Body: The necromancer sheds his life's shell and temporarily gains the undead subtype. While under this effect the necromancer loses his constitution score and gain the traits of an undead creature. This effect renders the necromancer medically dead for its duration.
Mind: The necromancer gains spell resistance equal to 10 + necromancer level. Furthermore, any time the necromancer is forced to make a Will save, he may roll twice and take the best of both roll.
Destruction Retribution		KEY:xxx ~ 				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:xxx Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Supernatural	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:At 16th level, when any undead the necromancer summoned is destroyed, it releases a burst of dark energy upon its destruction, dealing 1d6 points of shadow damage plus an additional 1d6 points per 2 Hit Dice to every creature within a 10-foot burst, a Reflex save (DC 10 + half the undead's Hit Dice + necromancer's Charisma modifier) for half damage.
Deathly Abeyance		KEY:xxx ~ 				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:xxx Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Supernatural	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:At 17th level, the necromancer can hold the spirits of death at bay, preventing an ally from dying. A number of times per day equal to the necromancer's Charisma modifier, as an immediate reaction, he can grant a creature within 30 feet that would die a second chance at life. If the target would die from an attack that deals damage, the necromancer can take the damage onto himself, preventing the ally from dying.
If the target would die as a result of a failed saving throw, the necromancer grants the target an immediate second saving throw. If the die roll of the second saving throw is a 1-10, the target adds +10 to the die roll (resulting in a die roll that must fall between 11-20). If the second save succeeds, the target does not die, though it suffers any other consequence of the effect. If the second save fails, the target still dies.
Final Guide		KEY:xxx ~ 				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:xxx Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Supernatural	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:At 19th level, a necromancer can actually guide the spirit of a slain creature back to its body a number of times per day equal to the necromancer's Charisma modifier, restoring the creature to life. This is only possible if the spirit is nearby, and thus this power must be used within 10 minutes since the creature's death. This functions like the Arise spell except the casting time is 1 full round. Once a creature has been restored to life by a necromancer's final guide ability, that creature cannot benefit from that ability again (from any necromancer) until 24 hours has passed.
# 170 of 907
Undead Transformation		KEY:xxx ~ 				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:xxx Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Supernatural	SOURCEPAGE:p.170	DESC:When a necromancer attains 20th level, he undergoes a hideous transformation and becomes an undead creature. The necromancer chooses an undead template (for example, vampire, lich, ghoul, zombie, skeleton, etc.). Once chosen, the template is permanent. If experience or gil is needed to pay for the template, the necromancer isn't require to do so.

###Block - Red Mage Class Feature
Weapon and Armor Proficiency	KEY:Red Mage ~ Weapon and Armor Proficiency					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Red Mage Class Feature.SpecialQuality			SOURCEPAGE:p.171	DESC:Red Mages are proficient with all simple and martial weapons including power rods and power staves. They are also proficient with light armor, medium armor, and shields (except tower shields).
Limit Breaks			KEY:Red Mage ~ Limit Breaks								CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Red Mage Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Supernatural	SOURCEPAGE:p.171	DESC:At 1st level, the red mage receives the Limit Breaks (Dual Spells and Flexibility).
Dual Spellcasting			KEY:Red Mage ~ Dual Spellcasting							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Red Mage Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Supernatural	SOURCEPAGE:p.171	DESC:This Limit Break allows the red mage to cast a healing spell and a damage spell in the same round for a duration of 1 round + 1 round per four red mage levels. MP must be paid for both spells. This limit break requires only a swift action.
Flexibility				KEY:Red Mage ~ Flexibility								CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Red Mage Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Supernatural	SOURCEPAGE:p.171	DESC:This Limit Break allows the red mage to change his current HP total and current MP total on the fly. As an immediate action for a duration of 1 round + 1 round per four red mage levels, the red mage can swap any number of points from HP to MP or from MP to HP on a 1 for 1 basis. The red mage cannot swap below 1 hit point. This limit break requires only a swift action.
Spells				KEY:Red Mage ~ Spells									CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Red Mage Class Feature.SpecialQuality			SOURCEPAGE:p.171	DESC:A red mage casts red magic spells which are drawn from the red mage spell list. A red mage begins play with 2 1st level red mage spells of his choice. At each new red mage level, he gains one new spell of any spell level or levels that he can cast (based on his new red mage level). Like most mages, a red mage can find or purchase scrolls with spells to add to his repertoire. To learn or cast a red mage spell, the red mage must have a Charisma score equal to at least 10 + the spell level (Cha 11 for 1st-level spells, Cha 12 for 2nd-level spells, and so forth). The Difficulty Class for a saving throw against a red mage's spell is 10 + the spell level + the red mage's Charisma modifier. In addition, a red mage gains additional MP for having a high attribute (Charisma).
Red Magery				KEY:Red Mage ~ Red Magery								CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Red Mage Class Feature.SpecialQuality			SOURCEPAGE:p.171	DESC:At 1st, 5th, 9th, 13th, and 17th level, a red mage increases his power with his spells. At each such opportunity, he can choose from the list of the following (with a limit of 2 per):
Spell Proficiency			KEY:Red Mage ~ Spell Proficiency							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Red Mage Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	SOURCEPAGE:p.172	DESC:Red mages are considered to have the Precise Shot feat while casting spells or using any magical items that require ranged touch.
Cantrips				KEY:Red Mage ~ Cantrips									CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Red Mage Class Feature.SpecialQuality			SOURCEPAGE:p.172	DESC:Red mages learn a number of cantrips, or 0-level spells. These spells are cast like any other spell, but they do not consume MP and may be used again. Red mages begin with 2 0-level spells and gain an additional 0-level spell every four levels after 1st level.
Ruby Knowledge			KEY:Red Mage ~ Ruby Knowledge								CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Red Mage Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	SOURCEPAGE:p.172	DESC:A red mage is specialized in dealing and healing damage with his spells. Whenever a red mage casts a spell that deals hit point dice damage, he adds his Intelligence bonus (if any) to the amount of damage dealt. Whenever a red mage casts a spell that heals hit point dice damage, he adds his Wisdom bonus (if any) to the damage healed. A single spell can never gain this extra damage or healing more than once per casting. If a spell deals or heals damage for more than 1 round, it does not gain the benefit of the ruby knowledge ability. The bonus from the this ability applies only to spells that he casts as a red mage, not to those he might have by virtue of levels in another class.
Spell Combat			KEY:Red Mage ~ Spell Combat								CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Red Mage Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	SOURCEPAGE:p.172	DESC:At 1st level, a red mage learns to cast spells and wield his weapons at the same time. This functions much like two-weapon fighting, but the off-hand weapon is a spell that is being cast. To use this ability, the red mage must have one hand free, while wielding a light or one-handed melee weapon in the other hand. As a full-round action, he can make all of his attacks with his melee weapon at a -4 penalty and can also cast any spell from his red mage spell list with a casting time of 1 standard action (any attack roll made as part of this spell also takes this penalty). If he casts this spell defensively, he can decide to take an additional penalty on his attack rolls, up to his Charisma bonus, and add the same amount as a circumstance bonus on his Concentration check. If the check fails, the spell is wasted, but the attacks still take the penalty. A red mage can choose to cast the spell first or make the weapon attacks first, but if he has more than one attack, he cannot cast the spell between weapon attacks.
Arcane Pool				KEY:Red Mage ~ Arcane Pool								CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Red Mage Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Supernatural	SOURCEPAGE:p.172	DESC:At 2nd level, the red mage gains a reservoir of mystical arcane energy that he can draw upon to fuel his powers and enhance his weapon. This arcane pool has a number of points equal to 1/2 his red mage level (minimum 1) + his Charisma modifier. The pool refreshes once per day when the red mage rests for a full 8 hours. At 2nd level, a red mage can expend 1 point from his arcane pool as a swift action to grant any weapon he is holding a +1 enhancement bonus for 1 minute. For every four levels beyond 2nd the weapon gains another +1 enhancement bonus, to a maximum of +5 at 18th level. These bonuses can be added to the weapon, stacking with existing weapon enhancement to a maximum of +5. Multiple uses of this ability do not stack with themselves. At 6th level, these bonuses can be used to add any of the following weapon properties: dancing, flaming, flaming burst, frost, icy burst, keen, shock, shocking burst, speed, or vorpal. Adding these properties consumes an amount of bonus equal to the property's base price modifier. These properties are added to any the weapon already has, but duplicates do not stack. If the weapon is not magical, at least a +1 enhancement bonus must be added before any other properties can be added. These bonuses and properties are decided when the arcane pool point is spent and cannot be changed until the next time the red mage uses this ability. These bonuses do not function if the weapon is wielded by anyone other than the red mage. A red mage can only enhance one weapon in this way at one time. If he uses this ability again, the first use immediately ends.
Quick Learner (Minor)		KEY:Red Mage ~ Quick Learner (Minor)						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Red Mage Class Feature.SpecialQuality			SOURCEPAGE:p.173	DESC:At 2nd and 6th level, a red mage chooses one of the following abilities to add to his list of class features:
Spellstrike				KEY:Red Mage ~ Spellstrike								CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Red Mage Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Supernatural	SOURCEPAGE:p.173	DESC:At 2nd level, whenever a red mage casts a single-target spell, he can deliver the spell through any weapon he is wielding as part of a melee attack. Instead of the free melee touch attack normally allowed to deliver the spell, a red mage can make one free melee attack with his weapon (at his highest base attack bonus) as part of casting this spell. If successful, this melee attack deals its normal damage as well as the effects of the spell. If the red mage makes this attack in concert with spell combat, this melee attack takes all the penalties accrued by spell combat melee attacks. This attack uses the weapon's critical range (20, 19-20, or 18-20 and modified by the keen weapon property or similar effects), but the spell effect only deals x2 damage on a successful critical hit, while the weapon damage uses its own critical modifier.
Armored Mage			KEY:Red Mage ~ Armored Mage								CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Red Mage Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	SOURCEPAGE:p.173	DESC:At 3rd level, normally, armor heavier than light armor interferes with a spell-caster's gestures, which can cause spells to fail if those spells have a somatic component. A red mage's limited focus and specialized training, however, allows him to avoid spell failure so long as he sticks to light armor and light shields. This training does not extend to medium armor or to heavy shields. This ability does not apply to spells gained from a different spell-casting class. At 7th level, a red mage learns to use medium armor with no chance of spell failure. At 10th level, a red mage learns to use heavy shields with no chance of spell failure.
Ruby Arcana				KEY:Red Mage ~ Ruby Arcana								CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Red Mage Class Feature.SpecialQuality			SOURCEPAGE:p.173	DESC:As he gains levels, a red mage learns arcane secrets tailored to his specific way of blending martial puissance and magical skill. Starting at 3rd level, a red mage gains one ruby arcana. He gains an additional ruby arcana for every three levels of red mage attained after 3rd level. Unless specifically noted in a ruby arcana's description, a red mage cannot select a particular ruby arcana more than once. Ruby arcana that affect spells can only be used to modify spells from the red mage spell list unless otherwise noted.
Quick Cast				KEY:Red Mage ~ Quick Cast								CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Red Mage Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	SOURCEPAGE:p.177	DESC:Beginning at 4th level, a red mage can cast one spell each day as a swift action, so long as the casting time of the spell is 1 standard action or less. He can use this ability twice per day at 8th level, three times per day at 12th level, and four times per day at 16th level.
Convert				KEY:Red Mage ~ Convert									CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Red Mage Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	SOURCEPAGE:p.177	DESC:Beginning of 5th level, a red mage can convert hit points into MP as a free action. For every 5 hit points converted, the red mage receives 1 MP. The red mage cannot convert below 1 hit point and can only convert MP equal to his red mage level. The red mage can use this ability a number of times per day equal to his Charisma modifier.
Improved Spell Combat		KEY:Red Mage ~ Improved Spell Combat						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Red Mage Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	SOURCEPAGE:p.177	DESC:At 8th level, the red mage's ability to cast spells and make melee attacks improves. When using the spell combat ability, the red mage receives a +2 circumstance bonus on concentration checks, in addition to any bonus granted by taking an additional penalty on the attack roll.
Clear Mind				KEY:Red Mage ~ Clear Mind								CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Red Mage Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	SOURCEPAGE:p.177	DESC:At 10th level, a red mage can regain his MP quicker. The red mage must be relaxed and must be free from overt distractions, such as combat raging nearby or other loud noises. The red mage regains MP equaling to his Charisma modifier per hour.
Quick Learner (Moderate)	KEY:Red Mage ~ Quick Learner (Moderate)						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Red Mage Class Feature.SpecialQuality			SOURCEPAGE:p.177	DESC:At 10th and 14th level, the red mage may add one of the following abilities to his list of class features.
Fighter Training			KEY:Red Mage ~ Fighter Training							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Red Mage Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	SOURCEPAGE:p.177	DESC:Starting at 11th level, a red mage counts half his total red mage level as his fighter level for the purpose of qualifying for feats. If he has levels in fighter, these levels stack.
Jack-of-All-Trades		KEY:Red Mage ~ Jack-of-All-Trades							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Red Mage Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	SOURCEPAGE:p.178	DESC:Also at 11th level, the red mage can use any skill, even if the skill normally requires him to be trained. At 15th level, the red mage considers all skills to be class skills. At 19th level, the red mage can take 10 on any skill check, even if it is not normally allowed.
Greater Spell Combat		KEY:Red Mage ~ Greater Spell Combat							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Red Mage Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	SOURCEPAGE:p.178	DESC:At 14th level, the red mage gains the ability to seamlessly cast spells and make melee attacks. Whenever he uses the spell combat ability, his concentration check bonus equals double the amount of the attack penalty taken.
Doublecast				KEY:Red Mage ~ Doublecast								CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Red Mage Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Supernatural	SOURCEPAGE:p.178	DESC:Also at 15th level, once per day, a red mage can take a full-round action to cast two spells. The red mage pays MP for both spells as normal and if a concentration check is needed, he must check for both spells. He must also indicate the targets before spells are resolved.
Counterstrike			KEY:Red Mage ~ Counterstrike								CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Red Mage Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	SOURCEPAGE:p.178	DESC:At 16th level, whenever an enemy within reach of the red mage successfully casts a spell defensively, that enemy provokes an attack of opportunity from the red mage after the spell is complete. This attack of opportunity cannot disrupt the spell.
1 MP Spell				KEY:Red Mage ~ 1 MP Spell								CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Red Mage Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Supernatural	SOURCEPAGE:p.178	DESC:At 18th level, three times per day, as a move action, a red mage can reduce the cost of spells to 1 MP. Once activated, any spells the red mage casts only cost 1 MP. This ability ends at the end of the round.
Quick Learner (Major)		KEY:Red Mage ~ Quick Learner (Major)						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Red Mage Class Feature.SpecialQuality			SOURCEPAGE:p.178	DESC:At 19th level, the red mage may add one of the following abilities to his list of class features:
Red Wizard				KEY:Red Mage ~ Red Wizard								CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Red Mage Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Supernatural	SOURCEPAGE:p.178	DESC:At 20th level, the red mage becomes a master of spells and combat. Whenever he uses his spell combat ability, he does not need to make a concentration check to cast the spell defensively. Whenever the red mage uses spell combat and his spell targets the same creature as his melee attacks, he can choose to either increase the DC to resist the spell by +2, grant himself a +2 circumstance bonus on any checks made to overcome spell resistance, or grant himself a +2 circumstance bonus on all attack rolls made against the target during his turn.

# Red Magery
Extra Quick Casts			KEY:Red Magery ~ Extra Quick Casts							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Red Magery.SpecialQuality			SOURCEPAGE:p.171	DESC:This grants the red mage an additional use of Quick Cast per day.
Quick Mind				KEY:Red Magery ~ Quick Mind								CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Red Magery.SpecialQuality			SOURCEPAGE:p.171	DESC:This grants the red mage an additional swift or immediate action per round.
Ruby Knowledge Mastery		KEY:Red Magery ~ Ruby Knowledge Mastery						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Red Magery.SpecialQuality			SOURCEPAGE:p.172	DESC:This increases the stat bonus to spells as if your casting attribute were four points higher.
Spell Combat Expertise		KEY:Red Magery ~ Spell Combat Expertise						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Red Magery.SpecialQuality			SOURCEPAGE:p.172	DESC:This lowers the attack penalty by 2.

# Quick Learner (Minor)
Advanced Learning			KEY:Quick Learner ~ Minor ~ Advanced Learning							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Quick Learner (Minor).SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	SOURCEPAGE:p.173	DESC:The red mage can add a new spell from the black or white mage spell list to his list with a level of his highest known spell level or lower. He may select this special ability multiple times, each time he adds a different spell to his spells known.
Bonus Metamagic Feat		KEY:Quick Learner ~ Minor ~ Bonus Metamagic Feat						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Quick Learner (Minor).SpecialQuality			SOURCEPAGE:p.173	DESC:The red mage gains a bonus metamagic feat he meets the prerequisites for.
Weapon Bond				KEY:Quick Learner ~ Minor ~ Weapon Bond								CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Quick Learner (Minor).SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	SOURCEPAGE:p.173	DESC:The red mage selects one weapon he is proficient with. He gains Weapon Focus with this weapon, even if he does not meet the prerequisites for it. The red mage can only take this ability once.

# Ruby Arcana
Accurate Strike			KEY:Ruby Arcana ~ Accurate Strike							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ruby Arcana.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	SOURCEPAGE:p.173	DESC:The Ruby Arcana can expend 2 points from his arcane pool as a swift action to resolve all of his melee weapon attacks until the end of his turn as melee touch attacks. Prerequisite: Ruby Arcana 9
Aquatic Agility			KEY:Ruby Arcana ~ Aquatic Agility							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ruby Arcana.SpecialQuality.Supernatural	SOURCEPAGE:p.173	DESC:Benefit: As an immediate action, the Ruby Arcana can spend 1 point from his arcane pool to gain the benefits of water breathing for 1 round per level. During this time, he can ignore the effects of rough water and underwater combat on his attacks and movement. Prerequisite: Ruby Arcana 6
Arcane Accuracy			KEY:Ruby Arcana ~ Arcane Accuracy							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ruby Arcana.SpecialQuality.Supernatural	SOURCEPAGE:p.174	DESC:The Ruby Arcana can expend 1 point from his arcane pool as a swift action to grant himself an insight bonus equal to his Charisma bonus on all attack rolls until the end of his turn.
Arcane Cloak			KEY:Ruby Arcana ~ Arcane Cloak							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ruby Arcana.SpecialQuality.Supernatural	SOURCEPAGE:p.174	DESC:The Ruby Arcana can expend 1 point from his arcane pool to add his Charisma bonus to Stealth checks and Bluff checks to create a diversion in order to hide. This bonus lasts for 1 minute.
Arcane Dealer			KEY:Ruby Arcana ~ Arcane Dealer							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ruby Arcana.SpecialQuality.Supernatural	SOURCEPAGE:p.174	DESC:The Ruby Arcana gains the Deadly Dealer feat, even if he does not meet the prerequisites. He can use his arcane pool to grant a deck of cards an enhancement bonus as though it were a ranged weapon with 54 pieces of ammunition. The Ruby Arcana must use either Arcane Strike or his arcane pool to enhance the cards in order to use them as weapons. Prerequisite: Ruby Arcana 6
Arcane Edge				KEY:Ruby Arcana ~ Arcane Edge								CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ruby Arcana.SpecialQuality.Supernatural	SOURCEPAGE:p.174	DESC:The Ruby Arcana can expend 1 point from his arcane pool as an immediate action after hitting a target with a slashing or piercing weapon in order to deal an amount of bleed damage equal to his Intelligence modifier (minimum 0). Prerequisite: Ruby Arcana 9
Arcane Redoubt			KEY:Ruby Arcana ~ Arcane Redoubt							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ruby Arcana.SpecialQuality.Supernatural	SOURCEPAGE:p.174	DESC:As a swift action, the Ruby Arcana can expend 1 point from his arcane pool to treat his shield bonus to AC (including any enhancement bonus) as a bonus to touch AC until the beginning of his next turn.
Arcane Redoubt, Greater		KEY:Ruby Arcana ~ Arcane Redoubt, Greater						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ruby Arcana.SpecialQuality.Supernatural	SOURCEPAGE:p.174	DESC:Whenever the Ruby Arcana uses his arcane redoubt ruby arcana, he may spend an additional point from his arcane pool in order to apply his shield bonus to AC (including any enhancement bonus) as a bonus on Reflex saves until the beginning of his next turn. If he is targeted with an effect requiring a Reflex save while using this power, he may spend 2 points from his arcane pool as an immediate action to grant himself evasion, or 4 points to grant himself improved evasion. Prerequisite: Ruby Arcana 12, arcane redoubt ruby arcana
Bane Blade				KEY:Ruby Arcana ~ Bane Blade								CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ruby Arcana.SpecialQuality.Supernatural	SOURCEPAGE:p.174	DESC:Whenever the Ruby Arcana enhances his weapon using his arcane pool, he may spend 1 additional point from his arcane pool to add the bane special ability to the weapon. Prerequisite: Ruby Arcana 15
Broad Study				KEY:Ruby Arcana ~ Broad Study								CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ruby Arcana.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	SOURCEPAGE:p.174	DESC:The Ruby Arcana selects another one of his spellcasting classes. The Ruby Arcana can use his spell combat abilities while casting or using spells from the spell list of that class. Prerequisite: Ruby Arcana 6, levels in another spellcasting class
Concentrate				KEY:Ruby Arcana ~ Concentrate								CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ruby Arcana.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	SOURCEPAGE:p.174	DESC:The Ruby Arcana can reroll any concentration check he has just made with a +4 bonus. He must use this ability after the roll is made, but before the roll's outcome is determined. The Ruby Arcana must take the second roll, even if it is worse. The Ruby Arcana can use this ability once per day.
Devoted Blade			KEY:Ruby Arcana ~ Devoted Blade							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ruby Arcana.SpecialQuality.Supernatural	SOURCEPAGE:p.174	DESC:Whenever the Ruby Arcana enhances his weapon using his arcane pool, he may spend 1 additional point from his arcane pool to add either the anarchic, axiomatic, holy, or unholy special ability to the list of available options. A Ruby Arcana may only add one of these abilities if it matches his own alignment. Prerequisite: Ruby Arcana 12
Dispelling Strike			KEY:Ruby Arcana ~ Dispelling Strike							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ruby Arcana.SpecialQuality.Supernatural	SOURCEPAGE:p.174	DESC:The Ruby Arcana can spend 1 or more points from his arcane pool as a swift action to imbue his weapon with a special power. If the weapon strikes a creature within the next minute, that creature is the subject of a targeted dispel using the Ruby Arcana's level as the caster level, except that this effect cannot dispel a spell of a level higher than the number of arcane pool points expended to activate this ability (treat higher-level spells as if they do not exist and apply the dispel attempt to the remaining spells with the highest caster level). Once the strike is made, the power dissipates, even if the dispel attempt is unsuccessful. Prerequisite: Ruby Arcana 9
Disruptive				KEY:Ruby Arcana ~ Disruptive								CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ruby Arcana.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	SOURCEPAGE:p.175	DESC:The Ruby Arcana gains Disruptive as a bonus feat.
Enduring Blade			KEY:Ruby Arcana ~ Enduring Blade							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ruby Arcana.SpecialQuality.Supernatural	SOURCEPAGE:p.175	DESC:Whenever the Ruby Arcana enchants his weapon using his arcane pool, he may spend 1 additional point from his arcane pool to increase the duration to 1 minute per Ruby Arcana level. Prerequisite: Ruby Arcana 6
Empowered Magic			KEY:Ruby Arcana ~ Empowered Magic							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ruby Arcana.SpecialQuality.Supernatural	SOURCEPAGE:p.175	DESC:The Ruby Arcana can cast one spell per day as if it were modified by the Empower Spell feat. This does not increase the MP cost or the level of the spell. Prerequisite: Ruby Arcana 6
Familiar				KEY:Ruby Arcana ~ Familiar								CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ruby Arcana.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	SOURCEPAGE:p.175	DESC:The Ruby Arcana gains a familiar. This familiar follows the rules for familiars presented here.
Ghost Blade				KEY:Ruby Arcana ~ Ghost Blade								CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ruby Arcana.SpecialQuality.Supernatural	SOURCEPAGE:p.175	DESC:Whenever the Ruby Arcana enchants his weapon using his arcane pool, he may spend 1 additional point from his arcane pool to add the brilliant energy and ghost touch special abilities to the list of available options. Prerequisite: Ruby Arcana 9
Hasted Assault			KEY:Ruby Arcana ~ Hasted Assault							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ruby Arcana.SpecialQuality.Supernatural	SOURCEPAGE:p.175	DESC:The Ruby Arcana can expend 1 point from his arcane pool as a swift action to move more quickly. This functions as haste, but only targets the Ruby Arcana and lasts for a number of rounds equal to the Ruby Arcana's Charisma bonus. Prerequisite: Ruby Arcana 9
Ki Arcana				KEY:Ruby Arcana ~ Ki Arcana								CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ruby Arcana.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	SOURCEPAGE:p.175	DESC:The Ruby Arcana may use points from his arcana pool and ki points from a ki pool granted by another class interchangeably. Prerequisite: Ruby Arcana 6, must also have levels in a class that grants a ki pool
Lingering Pain			KEY:Ruby Arcana ~ Lingering Pain							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ruby Arcana.SpecialQuality.Supernatural	SOURCEPAGE:p.175	DESC:The Ruby Arcana can expend 1 point from his arcane pool as an immediate action after hitting a target with a weapon attack. All damage from that attack is considered continuous damage for the purposes of any concentration checks made by the target prior to the beginning of the Ruby Arcana's next turn.
Maneuver Mastery			KEY:Ruby Arcana ~ Maneuver Mastery							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ruby Arcana.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	SOURCEPAGE:p.175	DESC:The Ruby Arcana has mastered one combat maneuver. He selects one maneuver when selecting this arcana. Whenever he is attempting the selected maneuver, he uses his Ruby Arcana level in place of his base attack bonus (in addition to any base attack bonus gained from other classes). A Ruby Arcana can select this ruby arcana more than once. Its effects do not stack. Each time he selects this arcana, he selects another combat maneuver.
Maximized Magic			KEY:Ruby Arcana ~ Maximized Magic							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ruby Arcana.SpecialQuality.Supernatural	SOURCEPAGE:p.175	DESC:The Ruby Arcana can cast one spell per day as if it were modified by the Maximize Spell feat. This does not increase the MP cost or the level of the spell. Prerequisite: Ruby Arcana 12
Pool Strike				KEY:Ruby Arcana ~ Pool Strike								CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ruby Arcana.SpecialQuality.Supernatural	SOURCEPAGE:p.175	DESC:The Ruby Arcana can expend 1 point from his arcane pool as a standard action to charge his free hand with elemental energy. He can make a melee touch attack with that hand as a free action as part of activating this ability. If the touch attack hits, it releases the charge and deals 2d6 points of elemental damage (earth, fire, ice, lightning, water, or wind chosen when he spends the arcane pool point to activate this ability). If he misses with this attack, he can hold the charge for up to 1 minute before it dissipates. At 6th level, and every three levels thereafter, the amount of damage dealt by this attack increases by 1d6.
Pool Strike, Arcing		KEY:Ruby Arcana ~ Pool Strike, Arcing						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ruby Arcana.SpecialQuality.Supernatural	SOURCEPAGE:p.175	DESC:The Ruby Arcana can expend 1 additional point from his arcane pool when using the pool strike arcana. If his attack hits, the Ruby Arcana can target a number of enemies within 15 feet equal to his Charisma modifier (minimum 0) with a ranged touch attack as a free action. Those struck take the same elemental damage as the primary target of the pool strike, including increased damage on a critical hit. Prerequisite: Ruby Arcana 12, pool strike ruby arcana
Pool Strike, Clinging		KEY:Ruby Arcana ~ Pool Strike, Clinging						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ruby Arcana.SpecialQuality.Supernatural	SOURCEPAGE:p.176	DESC:The Ruby Arcana can expend 1 additional point from his arcane pool when making a pool strike. A single target of his pool strike takes elemental damage as normal from the pool strike and also takes half this amount of damage at the beginning of its turn on the following round. Prerequisite: Ruby Arcana 9, pool strike ruby arcana
Prescient Attack			KEY:Ruby Arcana ~ Prescient Attack							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ruby Arcana.SpecialQuality.Supernatural	SOURCEPAGE:p.176	DESC:The Ruby Arcana can expend 1 point from his arcane pool as an immediate action after hitting a target with a weapon attack, allowing him to anticipate his opponent's defenses. The target is denied its Dexterity bonus against the Ruby Arcana's attacks until the end of the Ruby Arcana's next turn. Prerequisite: Ruby Arcana 6
Prescient Defense			KEY:Ruby Arcana ~ Prescient Defense							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ruby Arcana.SpecialQuality.Supernatural	SOURCEPAGE:p.176	DESC:The Ruby Arcana can expend 1 point from his arcane pool as an immediate action after hitting a target with a weapon attack, granting him a premonition of his enemy's intentions. The Ruby Arcana gains a bonus to his AC and on Reflex saves equal to his Charisma modifier (minimum 0) against attacks by that opponent until the beginning of his next turn. Prerequisite: Ruby Arcana 9
Quickened Magic			KEY:Ruby Arcana ~ Quickened Magic							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ruby Arcana.SpecialQuality.Supernatural	SOURCEPAGE:p.176	DESC:The Ruby Arcana can cast one spell per day as if it were modified by the Quicken Spell feat. This does not increase the MP cost or the level of the spell. Prerequisite: Ruby Arcana 15
Reflection				KEY:Ruby Arcana ~ Reflection								CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ruby Arcana.SpecialQuality.Supernatural	SOURCEPAGE:p.176	DESC:The Ruby Arcana can sacrifice 1 or more points from his arcane pool as an immediate action to reflect a spell back at its caster. This functions as reflect, but only if the targeted spell is of a level equal to or lower than the number of points expended. If insufficient points are expended, they instead grant an insight bonus on any saving throws allowed by the spell, equal to the number of points spent. Prerequisite: Ruby Arcana 15
Rod Mastery				KEY:Ruby Arcana ~ Rod Mastery								CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ruby Arcana.SpecialQuality.Supernatural	SOURCEPAGE:p.176	DESC:Whenever the Ruby Arcana uses a rod, he calculates the DC for any spell it contains using his Charisma modifier (minimum 0) instead of the minimum modifier needed to cast a spell of that level.
Rod Wielder				KEY:Ruby Arcana ~ Rod Wielder								CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ruby Arcana.SpecialQuality.Supernatural	SOURCEPAGE:p.176	DESC:The Ruby Arcana adds his Charisma bonus (minimum 0) on caster level checks made to overcome spell resistance when using a spell contained within a rod.
Scroll Mastery			KEY:Ruby Arcana ~ Scroll Mastery							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ruby Arcana.SpecialQuality.Supernatural	SOURCEPAGE:p.176	DESC:Whenever the Ruby Arcana uses a scroll, he may expend 1 point from his arcane pool to allow him to calculate the DC for any spell contained on the scroll using his Intelligence modifier, instead of the minimum modifier needed cast a spell of that level. Prerequisite: Ruby Arcana 6
Silent Magic			KEY:Ruby Arcana ~ Silent Magic							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ruby Arcana.SpecialQuality.Supernatural	SOURCEPAGE:p.176	DESC:The Ruby Arcana can cast one spell per day as if it were modified by the Silent Spell feat. This does not increase the MP cost or the level of the spell.
Spell Blending			KEY:Ruby Arcana ~ Spell Blending							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ruby Arcana.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	SOURCEPAGE:p.176	DESC:When a Ruby Arcana selects this arcana, he must select one spell from the black or white mage spell list that is of a Ruby Arcana spell level he can cast. He adds this spell to his list of Ruby Arcana spells known as a Ruby Arcana spell of its black or white mage spell level. He can instead select two spells to add in this way, but both must be at least one level lower than the highest-level Ruby Arcana spell he can cast. A Ruby Arcana can select this Ruby Arcana arcana more than once.
Spell Shield			KEY:Ruby Arcana ~ Spell Shield							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ruby Arcana.SpecialQuality.Supernatural	SOURCEPAGE:p.176	DESC:The Ruby Arcana can expend a point from his arcane pool as an immediate action to grant himself a shield bonus to AC equal to his Charisma bonus until the end of his next turn.
